ERDF Projects

The Catalysis and Spectrochemistry laboratory has obtained 3 ERDF funding on
the following research themes:

ZEOXY project: Use of zeolites as gaseous reoxygenation therapy vehicles for
glioblasthomas.

BIOCAR project: 2nd generation biofuels: Ultimate purification of 2G biofuels
to limit emissions of toxic molecules at engine output.

DRUID project: Diagnosis of Reaction Mechanisms of Decontamination by
Catalysis.

SIRCO project :Efficient photocatalytic reduction of CO¬≤.


